  "text": "We illustrate the differences in the piecewise (PCW)-smooth solution spaces of the two models for two unweighted circulant graphs with N = 64 in Fig. 1(a) -(b). Here, two distinct quadratic polynomial atoms L † t with one discontinuity respectively at t = i, j are depicted in comparison to their difference, which gives rise to the linear signal with two discontinuities at i, j and, hence, 2-sparse analysis representation ei − ej with respect to L. The perturbation effect for the non-trivial circulant case in (b) is clearly visible around the discontinuities. Fig. 1(c) further depicts the linear signal from (b) in the vertex domain (prepared using [CITATION_1] ).",
